abstract: President Obama on Thursday called Kamala Harris, the California attorney general, and apologized to her for saying that she is the “best-looking attorney general in the country.”
snippet: President Obama on Thursday called Kamala Harris, the California attorney general, and apologized to her for saying that she is the “best-looking attorney general in the country.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Obama late Thursday night called Kamala Harris, the California attorney general, and apologized to her for telling a group of wealthy donors that she is the “best-looking attorney general in the country.”

abstract: President Obama, on a Democratic fund-raising trip to California, left behind a debate about whether he tripped over the line of political correctness by calling Kamala Harris “the best-looking attorney general in the country.”
snippet: President Obama, on a Democratic fund-raising trip to California, left behind a debate about whether he tripped over the line of political correctness by calling Kamala Harris “the best-looking attorney general in the country.”
lead_paragraph: President Obama headed out to California with a simple goal: to collect a few million dollars for Democrats. By the time Air Force One departed the state, however, he left behind a debate about whether he tripped over the line of political correctness.
headline_main: Obama’s Remarks About California’s Attorney General Raise Eyebrows

abstract: President Obama laid bare the political dilemma he faced on environmental issues, including the fate of the controversial Keystone XL pipeline from Canada.
snippet: President Obama laid bare the political dilemma he faced on environmental issues, including the fate of the controversial Keystone XL pipeline from Canada.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Appearing at the home of an outspoken critic of the Keystone XL pipeline, President Obama on Wednesday night told a group of high-dollar donors that the politics of the environment “are tough.”

abstract: Same-sex marriage’s turn before the Supreme Court and gun control headline the Sunday shows this week.
snippet: Same-sex marriage’s turn before the Supreme Court and gun control headline the Sunday shows this week.
lead_paragraph: As Congress heads off for a two-week recess, the Sunday shows take a look at the fight over gun control and the scheduled Supreme Court arguments over same-sex marriage.

abstract: Edward J. DeMarco, acting director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency, has been at odds with the White House over a proposal to reduce the principal on underwater mortgages.
snippet: Edward J. DeMarco, acting director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency, has been at odds with the White House over a proposal to reduce the principal on underwater mortgages.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Prominent state attorneys general are calling on President Obama to fire the acting director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency and name a new permanent director, arguing that current policies are impeding the economic recovery.

abstract: California’s attorney general is urging mobile app developers and their advertising partners to be transparent in how they collect and use personal data from cellphone users.
snippet: California’s attorney general is urging mobile app developers and their advertising partners to be transparent in how they collect and use personal data from cellphone users.
lead_paragraph: Make your privacy policy readable. Avoid collecting data that you don’t need for the app to function normally. Alert users with “enhanced measures” if third parties are collecting information, including for advertising.
headline_main: California Suggests Mobile App Privacy Guidelines

abstract: The Obama administration promises a stricter focus on deporting serious offenders.
snippet: The Obama administration promises a stricter focus on deporting serious offenders.
lead_paragraph: The Obama administration on Friday announced a policy change that — if it works — should lead to smarter enforcement of the immigration laws, with greater effort spent on deporting dangerous felons and less on minor offenders who pose no threat.

abstract: Only 20 percent of mobile apps for children provided disclosures about their data collection practices, according to a new Federal Trade Commission report.
snippet: Only 20 percent of mobile apps for children provided disclosures about their data collection practices, according to a new Federal Trade Commission report.
lead_paragraph: Several hundred of the most popular educational and gaming mobile apps for children fail to give parents basic explanations about what kinds of personal information the apps collect from children, who can see that data and what they use it for, a new federal report says.

abstract: Two contradictory judicial rulings suggest that a California ban on a treatment for minors could be embroiled in the courts for months.
snippet: Two contradictory judicial rulings suggest that a California ban on a treatment for minors could be embroiled in the courts for months.
lead_paragraph: A federal judge cleared the way on Tuesday for California’s new law banning gay “conversion therapies” for minors, one day after another federal judge, in a separate decision, called the ban an unconstitutional infringement on speech.
